reviewText: I watched this because I'm a longtime fan of one of the performers - Reggie Watts. I listened to his band Maktub years ago when I lived in Seattle.  A lot of performers, song & dance, an unmemorable soliliquy by Watts.  Very non-linear and made no sense. I'll stick to downloading Maktub's Amazon mp3s
This item arrived within the time set by amazon.  I enjoyed the young group that is singing traditional gospel quartet  music...with a modern twist!

This is a nice DVD but it's not what I ordered. I ordered The Transition not Transition Live.
Transition Live doesn't have part 1 & 2 of Somebody Prayed for Me. I bought this for a gift for someone.
V.Nelson

inspired talent and collaboration. wicked clever. if you're not sure what you're watching, just sit with it for a bit....(or speed through if you're a jerk like me) but give it approximately 13 minutes to kick in then enjoy the ride.
I've seen and heard a ton of what Reggie Watts has done and have enjoyed it. This was a whole new level of amazing! Very few are able to capture moments like this on video.
Not quite sure what to think of this, I love all of Reggie's other stuff but this is kind of out there.
I want this guy to play at my funeral
Great gospel group and fantastic music.
This is a young very talented group of gospel singers. I really enjoyed this concert.
